			<abstract label="Abstract:">Collection contains 16 pamphlets, booklets and newsletters
				on how to prepare for and survive a nuclear attack issued primarily by federal and
				state government agencies.</abstract>
			<langmaterial label="Language:">Collection material in <language encodinganalog="041" langcode="eng">English</language></langmaterial>
		</did>
		<bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
			<p>In the late 1950s and early 1960s, Cold War tensions and threat of nuclear war
				convinced government leaders in the United States that millions of lives could be
				saved by the construction of home fallout shelters. How-to booklets proliferated,
				instructing people in the fine points of building their own shelters, family
				preparations, first aid, and what to do in an emergency.</p>
		</bioghist>
		<scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
			<head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
			<p>Collection contains 16 pamphlets, booklets and newsletters on how to prepare for and
				survive a nuclear attack issued primarily by federal and state government
				agencies.</p>
		</scopecontent>
